				"title": "Targeting specific audiences with Spotify",
				"images": [
					{
						"caption": "# **Targeting specific audiences with Spotify**\nWhen using Spotify as an advertising platform, media agencies need to know that they can reach the exact audience that they want to, using **content targeting, demographic targeting** and **time and platform targeting.**\n\nSwipe to get an overview about each type of targeting, then continue through the lesson to look at them in more detail."
					},
					{
						"image": "fit_content_assets/1464823581656.jpg",
						"caption": "## **Content targeting**\nContent targeting means targeting users based on **what they are listening to.**\n\nContent targeting can be used to reach users with particular **habits, \u0003mindsets,** and **tastes** that align with an client's target audience."
					},
					{
						"image": "fit_content_assets/1464823595921.jpg",
						"caption": "## **Demographic targeting**\nAgencies can use demographic targeting to target users based on **who they are.**\n\nDemographic targeting can be used to confidently reach any audience **across mobile, desktop** and **connected devices.**"
					},
					{
						"image": "fit_content_assets/1464823644157.jpg",
						"caption": "## **Time and Platform targeting.**\nTime and platform targeting allows agencies to target users based on **when and how they are listening to music.** \n\nIt means that agencies can be sure that messages are delivered at the **right time** \u0003and on the **right platform.**"
					}
				],
