			"data": {
				"title": "**Time and platform targeting**\n\n<p style=\"font-size:0.63em;\", align=\"left\">Tap to explore the different ways Spotify advertising allows targeting a specific time or platform.</span>",
				"images": [
					{
						"image": "fit_content_assets/1464844866879.jpg",
						"content": "## **Daypart**\nSpotify listeners are engaged from **morning** to **night,** not just during traditional peak hours. \n\nUsing Spotify advertising, audiences can be reached at a time which suits the client's messaging, or complements their broadcast buys."
					},
					{
						"image": "fit_content_assets/1464844856926.jpg",
						"content": "## **Platform**\nCampaigns can be dynamically served to users based on their active **Spotify app platform** including iPhone, iPad, Android (all devices), Desktop, Web Player, and PlayStation®.\n\nAdverts can also be targeted based on users' **mobile operating system,** or **mobile carrier.**"
					},
					{
						"image": "fit_content_assets/1464844736903.png",
						"content": "## **Retargeting & Sequential Messaging**\n**Cross-platform retargeting** allows clients to re-message users based on previous engagement or exposure to adverts across **all Spotify app platforms.**\n\n**Sequential messaging** also allows delivery of longer-form brand and product narratives. "
					}
				],
